nineteenth century and how mobility represents the possibilities of social movement for African Americans. Together, these complementary essays look to Muybridge’s works as interventions in knowledge and experience and as opportunities to investigate larger social ramifications and possibilities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aCinematographerszUnited States. 0aFreedom of movementxSocial aspects. 0aPhotographerszUnited States. 7aPhotography / Individual Photographers / Essays.2bisacsh1 aCresswell, Tim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLee, Anthony W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOtt, John, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aOtt, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2022z9783110992793oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2022 Englishz978311099281608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076649340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520382442?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520382442423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520382442/original  a978-3-11-076649-3  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099281-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-